## K5. Inclusion/Exclusion (Inklusion/Exklusion)

### Core Problems
1. Given |A|=30, |B|=25, |A∩B|=12. Find |A∪B| and |A\B|.  
2. |A|=20, |B|=18, |C|=17, |A∩B|=7, |A∩C|=6, |B∩C|=5, |A∩B∩C|=3. Find |A∪B∪C|.  
3. How many integers ≤100 are divisible by 2, 3, or 5?  
4. Find derangements D₄.  
5. Find the number of surjective functions from a 5-element set to a 3-element set.

### Extra Practice
6. How many integers ≤200 are divisible by 4 or 6 but not by 12?  
7. How many 3-digit numbers contain at least one 7?  
8. How many 4-digit numbers have no repeated digits?  

